    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init(int width,
                 int height,
                 int speed,
                 java.lang.Boolean compare)
        Initializes the remaining data of Binary Search Tree after the tree has been created. Calls computeNodeCoordinates() and treeHeight(Node).
        Parameters:
        width - the width of the canvas, in general 600 and 1200 for compare mode
        height - the height of the canvas, default 700
        speed - the speed of the drawing, defaults to 1 Node/sec
        compare - if compare mode has been enabled or not

      • insert

        public Node insert(Node root,
                   java.lang.String s)
        Recursive routine to insert a new node into the tree. Binary Search Tree posses special properties. Data is feed as a string s later parsed to integer and inserted by comparision.
        Parameters:
        root - root node of the tree
        s - integers as string
        Returns:
        root node of the tree

      • drawInOrder

        public void drawInOrder(Node node,
                        java.lang.Boolean path)
        Recursive drawing routine to visualize Inorder Traversal of the tree. Animates one node at a time.
        Parameters:
        node - initially root node to be passed
        path - the path should be shown or not
